HEADWORD: Daymare
<hw>Day"mare`</hw> <pr>(d⟦amac⟧"m⟦acir⟧r`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Day</ets> + <ets>mare</ets> incubus.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<def>A kind of incubus which occurs during wakefulness, attended by the
peculiar pressure on the chest which characterizes nightmare.</def>
<rj><au>Dunglison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

